WEBVTT

00:30.405 --> 00:32.406
[GROWLING]

00:38.955 --> 00:40.289
[THUD]

00:40.957 --> 00:41.957
[DISTANT YELLING]

00:43.418 --> 00:44.418
[GROWLING]

01:03.980 --> 01:05.063
[CRACKLING]

01:05.230 --> 01:06.273
[SQUISHING]

01:22.040 --> 01:23.290
[DRIPPING]

02:01.204 --> 02:02.371
[SQUIRTING]

02:58.511 --> 02:59.845
[ALARM CLOCK BEEPING]

03:04.642 --> 03:05.642
[SHUTS OFF]

03:27.624 --> 03:28.790
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

03:30.919 --> 03:32.586
[OVER PHONE]
Ariel, this is Sara.

03:32.754 --> 03:35.547
How many voice mails do l have to leave
before you call back?

03:35.715 --> 03:37.841
Damn it, l need to talk to you.
Please, call me ba--

03:38.009 --> 03:39.760
[CELL PHONE BEEPS OFF]

03:55.026 --> 03:57.611
ARIEL: Ethan, listen.
Our circulation is up 6 percent.

03:57.779 --> 03:58.820
You wanna know why?

03:58.988 --> 04:02.824
Because I live on five hours' sleep and the
only man in my life is Mr. Coffee, okay?

04:02.992 --> 04:04.242
Hang on. Hi. Thanks.

04:04.410 --> 04:06.578
ARIEL:
If advertisers don't like the new rates...

04:06.746 --> 04:09.665
...then find a magazine
with bigger words and smaller pictures.

04:09.832 --> 04:10.874
Ethan, I gotta go.

04:11.042 --> 04:13.335
I’ll talk to you about it later.

04:14.212 --> 04:16.338
I am so glad you're here, Ariel.

04:16.505 --> 04:19.841
Pearl Jam's manager just called,
they wanna reschedule the interview.

04:20.009 --> 04:22.094
ARIEL: That's exactly why
I don't date musicians.

04:22.261 --> 04:25.389
Oh, and also, one more thing,
your sister called last night.

04:25.556 --> 04:25.749
I’ll shoot her an e-mail
when I get a chance.

04:25.750 --> 04:28.544
I’ll shoot her an e-mail
when I get a chance.

04:29.045 --> 04:31.505
Not bad.
Have the article on my desk by 3:00.

04:31.923 --> 04:35.342
Paul was hoping that you could make it
to the shoot later.

04:35.510 --> 04:36.844
Really, now?

04:37.012 --> 04:41.056
He says he wants creative input, but I think
he's looking for an excuse to see you.

04:41.224 --> 04:43.100
I thought all photographers were gay.

04:43.268 --> 04:46.395
Oh, well, for a gay guy,
he sure likes to stare at your ass.

04:50.233 --> 04:51.567
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

04:57.490 --> 04:58.699
Having fun?

04:59.075 --> 05:01.619
It's a tough job,
but someone's gotta do it.

05:02.037 --> 05:04.705
-Hey. Oh!
-Hey. Oh, come on.

05:05.540 --> 05:08.459
When faced with natural beauty,
I just can't help myself.

05:08.627 --> 05:12.296
-Does this rap ever work with women?
-It's not a rap if it's true.

05:12.464 --> 05:13.881
-Right.
PAUL: Huh.

05:15.884 --> 05:20.179
HAMMER: The Middle Ages were
a breeding ground for superstition.

05:20.639 --> 05:25.976
Visions of departed souls,
angels and devils were common.

05:26.144 --> 05:27.186
[CLEARS THROAT]

05:28.855 --> 05:30.314
[SLIDE PROJECTOR CLICKS]

05:32.067 --> 05:34.943
While the Church grew
in power and influence...

05:35.111 --> 05:39.073
...another movement began to spread
across the Continent like a dark plague:

05:39.407 --> 05:41.825
The cult of the demon Baphomet.

05:41.993 --> 05:45.120
The Inquisition forced the cult members
to go underground.

05:45.288 --> 05:48.165
And that's when the Baphomet idol
disappeared.

05:48.583 --> 05:53.087
The statue has been lost for centuries.
I've been trying to find it for decades.

05:53.421 --> 05:58.967
My search has taken me all across Europe
and deep into the Old World's bloody past.

05:59.469 --> 06:04.431
Man has always been drawn
to the dark side, which is good for me.

06:04.599 --> 06:06.600
Otherwise, I wouldn't be selling
any books today.

06:06.768 --> 06:07.851
[STUDENTS LAUGH]

06:08.019 --> 06:10.521
And after that shameless plug,
I thank you.

06:10.689 --> 06:12.523
[LOUD APPLAUSE]

06:12.691 --> 06:13.816
HAMMER:
Thank you.

06:14.359 --> 06:17.486
Woo! Yeah. Right on.

06:20.907 --> 06:25.119
Guys, guys, please, one at a time, really.
The book's not even that good.

06:25.787 --> 06:26.954
Ho, ho, ho.

06:28.540 --> 06:34.545
So, what does a girl have to do
to get her book signed?

06:36.214 --> 06:37.381
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

06:37.549 --> 06:39.216
HAMMER: Hold it.
MICHELLE: Oh! Okay.

06:39.384 --> 06:41.135
HAMMER:
Okay.

06:43.888 --> 06:45.222
Dr. Hammer.

06:45.390 --> 06:48.308
-Oh. Heh, heh, heh.
-Dude, can you knock?

06:48.476 --> 06:51.395
-Someone's working hard on their Ph.D.
-Fuck you, Kyle.

06:51.563 --> 06:52.646
[CHUCKLES]

06:52.856 --> 06:54.773
Cut it out, the both of you.

06:54.941 --> 06:56.316
What is it, Kyle?

06:56.860 --> 06:59.737
Oh, shit, sorry.
I thought this couldn't wait.

07:00.905 --> 07:03.323
It's about Sara Wolfe.

07:04.117 --> 07:05.159
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

07:05.326 --> 07:08.829
ARIEL: Sorry, sorry.
PAUL: No, no, it's okay.

07:09.789 --> 07:12.124
Mom, this isn't a good time.

07:13.918 --> 07:15.627
Mom?

07:16.129 --> 07:18.172
Mom, what's wrong?

07:30.101 --> 07:31.435
[ARIEL SOBS]

07:31.603 --> 07:33.437
PAUL:
Hey.

07:34.022 --> 07:35.939
Thanks.

07:38.109 --> 07:40.778
The neighbors found her
early this morning.

07:41.696 --> 07:44.615
The cops say she shot herself.

07:46.284 --> 07:48.619
I'm-- I'm so sorry.

07:48.787 --> 07:49.953
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

07:51.414 --> 07:55.459
You know, my sister needed to talk me,
and all I could think about was work.

07:56.461 --> 07:58.796
If there's anything you need, just....

07:59.422 --> 08:01.215
Are you free tonight?

08:08.556 --> 08:12.392
I really appreciate you coming along.
I don't think I could do this by myself.

08:12.560 --> 08:15.103
Yeah, I'm glad to help out.

08:18.233 --> 08:20.484
PAUL:
You sure you wanna do this?

08:21.361 --> 08:24.446
You know, Sara was trying to reach me
before she died.

08:24.614 --> 08:26.657
I need to know why.

08:35.875 --> 08:37.042
[PAUL GASPS]

08:44.342 --> 08:47.928
PAUL:
Holy shit.

08:56.437 --> 08:59.481
PAUL: Isn't this the house where
all those people died a few years ago?

08:59.649 --> 09:03.235
Yeah. My sister was one of the few
that made it out alive.

09:03.403 --> 09:05.362
I remember seeing it on the news.

09:05.530 --> 09:09.658
Steven Price flipped out,
went on a killing spree.

09:09.826 --> 09:11.702
Not what happened,
according to my sister.

09:11.870 --> 09:15.289
-What do you mean?
-Sara believed the house was haunted.

09:15.456 --> 09:18.667
That ghosts killed Price's party guests.

09:19.377 --> 09:21.503
Well, that's insane.

09:22.922 --> 09:25.215
That's why we stopped talking.

09:25.884 --> 09:27.217
[BREATHING]

09:31.055 --> 09:32.389
Sara?

09:37.478 --> 09:38.812
[GUNSHOT]

09:43.401 --> 09:44.860
[IN DEMONIC VOICE]
You must help them.

09:46.195 --> 09:49.406
Hey, what--? What is it?
Are you okay? What's wrong?

09:49.908 --> 09:53.660
-You didn't see that?
-See what?

09:55.622 --> 09:57.247
God, I think I'm losing my mind.

09:57.415 --> 09:59.666
HAMMER: That's exactly
what your sister used to say.

10:00.251 --> 10:03.170
ARIEL:
Who are you? What are you doing here?

10:03.338 --> 10:05.881
I'm here for the same reason you are.

10:06.049 --> 10:09.092
I wanna know
what really happened to your sister.

10:09.886 --> 10:11.428
My name is Dr. Richard Hammer.

10:11.596 --> 10:15.057
I teach archaeology
and medieval history at Forman College.

10:15.224 --> 10:17.434
Your sister contacted me two weeks ago.

10:19.020 --> 10:21.146
Contacted you about what?

10:21.314 --> 10:24.816
Sara had gotten hold of
Dr. Vannacutt's journal.

10:24.984 --> 10:27.110
Okay, I'm sorry, I still don't understand.

10:27.278 --> 10:30.739
-I've been trying to find the Baphomet idol--
-Wait, the what?

10:31.199 --> 10:34.117
It's a statue
of incredible archaeological value.

10:34.285 --> 10:36.286
I've been trying to find it for years now.

10:36.454 --> 10:40.457
According to Dr. Vannacutt's journal,
the statue is here in Los Angeles...

10:40.625 --> 10:42.876
...inside the hill house.

10:43.044 --> 10:47.005
Your sister was gonna come back
to the house and help me find it.

10:47.173 --> 10:48.840
Now I know you're full of shit.

10:49.008 --> 10:52.427
Sara would never go back to that house,
she was terrified of it.

10:52.929 --> 10:54.638
We're out of here.

10:55.556 --> 10:59.184
HAMMER: You're right.
Sara was afraid of the house.

10:59.352 --> 11:01.311
But she was ready to face her demons.

11:01.479 --> 11:02.980
Hey, back off.

11:05.733 --> 11:08.485
Ariel, do you know
what happened to Vannacutt's journal?

11:08.653 --> 11:11.154
How should I know?
Let go of the damn door.

11:11.322 --> 11:14.616
-Sara thought she was being followed.
-What are you talking about?

11:14.784 --> 11:17.703
The idol is worth millions
to the right collector.

11:17.870 --> 11:20.163
There could be other
interested parties out there.

11:20.873 --> 11:24.126
What are you saying, someone went after
my sister for this journal?

11:24.669 --> 11:28.130
All I'm saying is, be careful.

11:29.424 --> 11:30.424
[THUD]

11:45.287 --> 11:46.955
Thank you.

11:47.832 --> 11:49.124
For being you.

11:50.251 --> 11:52.252
Hey, it's....

12:10.187 --> 12:11.813
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

12:18.571 --> 12:20.238
ARIEL:
Night.

12:38.466 --> 12:40.175
What the...?

12:40.342 --> 12:41.342
[TIRES SCREECHING]

12:41.510 --> 12:42.635
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

12:47.475 --> 12:48.641
[EXHALES]

12:55.566 --> 12:59.110
Sara, what were you up to?

13:05.075 --> 13:06.117
The journal.

13:06.285 --> 13:07.368
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

13:09.330 --> 13:10.330
ARIEL:
Paul?

13:13.626 --> 13:15.835
-You're never gonna believe this.
PAUL: Ariel, don't--!

13:16.212 --> 13:17.545
[GRUNTS]

13:18.047 --> 13:19.214
Hey.

13:19.381 --> 13:21.049
[PAUL GRUNTING]

13:22.510 --> 13:24.385
ARIEL:
Let him go!

13:25.221 --> 13:26.387
ARIEL:
Hey!

13:26.555 --> 13:27.847
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:30.559 --> 13:31.893
-Leave her the fuck alone.
-Yeah?

13:32.061 --> 13:33.061
[GUN COCKS]

13:33.229 --> 13:34.395
What are you gonna do?

13:34.688 --> 13:38.066
You gonna take a picture of me while
I put a fucking bullet in your head? Hmm?

13:41.070 --> 13:42.445
MAN 1 :
Sit down.

14:01.799 --> 14:02.924
[CHUCKLES]

14:03.884 --> 14:07.136
MAN 2:
Ah, yes. Your little magazine.

14:07.304 --> 14:08.304
Wow.

14:09.139 --> 14:11.266
You should be proud.

14:12.935 --> 14:14.102
Oh.

14:14.979 --> 14:17.855
What?
I swear, I only read it for the articles.

14:18.399 --> 14:19.732
[MAN CHUCKLES]

14:22.778 --> 14:26.948
-Who the hell are you people?
-Well, let's just say we're art lovers.

14:27.449 --> 14:31.703
-You're after the Baphomet statue.
-Bingo, give that girl a prize.

14:31.870 --> 14:36.958
-You're the bastard who killed my sister.
-That's not what the police say. Not at all.

14:37.126 --> 14:40.003
But I must admit, the suicide note?
Oh.

14:40.754 --> 14:42.964
That was inspired.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.299
[LAUGHS]

14:45.050 --> 14:46.884
[ARIEL GRUNTS]

14:47.094 --> 14:48.094
[GUNS COCK]

14:48.762 --> 14:49.762
[MAN GROANS]

14:51.974 --> 14:54.601
I think Helmut Newton here
has got the hots for his boss.

14:54.768 --> 14:56.894
You're gonna pay
for what you did to my sister.

14:57.062 --> 14:59.606
Oh, let's not get abusive,
now, sweetheart.

14:59.773 --> 15:05.236
I urged your sister to cooperate.
She chose to be a bitch.

15:05.404 --> 15:08.323
I highly suggest
you don't follow her example.

15:11.869 --> 15:13.661
Let's go, kids.

15:14.121 --> 15:15.121
[GRUNTING]

15:15.289 --> 15:16.623
Get up. Come on.

15:17.041 --> 15:18.416
Come on.

15:18.584 --> 15:21.252
-Get up. Come on.
ARIEL: What are you doing?

15:21.420 --> 15:24.339
Looks like the two of you
are gonna be joining us on a trip.

15:24.506 --> 15:26.507
Why? You got what you came for.

15:26.675 --> 15:28.343
I can't have you running
to the cops.

15:29.011 --> 15:34.682
I seriously doubt the authorities would fall
for yet another suicide in the family.

15:34.850 --> 15:36.017
Do you?

16:23.482 --> 16:25.400
Pretty creepy, isn't it?

16:25.567 --> 16:28.820
You know, they say that the souls
of the people who died here...

16:28.987 --> 16:31.197
...apparently still haunt the house.

16:31.365 --> 16:34.742
They also say that people who
believe in ghosts should be on Prozac.

16:36.203 --> 16:39.163
I'm sorry, I wasn't listening,
I was looking at your breasts.

16:39.331 --> 16:40.915
Kyle.

16:44.211 --> 16:47.505
So why is it that this can't wait
till tomorrow, again?

16:47.673 --> 16:50.383
The journal is missing
and I'm not taking any chances.

16:50.551 --> 16:53.052
If the Baphomet idol really is here...

16:53.220 --> 16:56.472
...you think I'm gonna let someone else
walk away with the prize?

17:10.112 --> 17:12.280
It’ll be okay.

17:13.741 --> 17:16.451
You make a beautiful couple.

17:21.790 --> 17:22.957
[GHOSTLY BREATHS]

17:25.627 --> 17:26.627
[MICE SQUEAKING]

17:29.006 --> 17:30.006
KYLE:
Wow.

17:31.383 --> 17:32.550
[KYLE EXHALES]

17:34.970 --> 17:36.721
This place is gnarly.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.306
Ironic, isn't it?

17:38.474 --> 17:39.974
Years of searching the globe...

17:40.142 --> 17:42.560
...when I should've been looking
in my own backyard.

17:42.728 --> 17:43.895
[GLASS CLINKS]

17:44.062 --> 17:45.354
Uh, question.

17:45.522 --> 17:46.814
HAMMER:
What?

17:46.982 --> 17:50.568
How does a medieval artifact end up
in Vannacutt's loony bin, anyway?

17:50.736 --> 17:53.905
Vannacutt was a big art collector,
traveled all across the world.

17:54.072 --> 17:56.324
He believed art could be therapeutic.

17:56.492 --> 17:59.452
You know, soothe disturbed minds.

17:59.620 --> 18:04.916
Heh. Isn't that the way you feel about
your action-figure collection, Kyle?

18:05.501 --> 18:07.335
Ow. Not funny.

18:26.063 --> 18:28.147
Lovely, isn't it?

18:28.607 --> 18:31.943
HAMMER: Who needs the journal when
you got the best gear money can buy?

18:32.110 --> 18:36.322
Now, listen up, class.
GPR, ground-penetrating radar.

18:36.490 --> 18:38.366
Emits an electromagnetic signal.

18:38.534 --> 18:41.661
Allows you to locate anomalies
or hollow spaces.

18:41.829 --> 18:43.037
KYLE:
Huh.

18:43.205 --> 18:44.664
[MAKES BEEPING SOUNDS]

18:46.041 --> 18:47.542
[MAKES FASTER BEEPING SOUNDS]

18:47.709 --> 18:49.502
Oh, my God, you're right. It so works.

18:49.670 --> 18:50.837
[LAUGHS]

18:51.964 --> 18:54.590
MAN:
All right. You're coming with us.

18:54.758 --> 18:56.801
-Why?
-Well, your sister was obsessed...

18:56.969 --> 18:58.678
...with the house. Um....

18:58.846 --> 19:01.639
I figure she told you a thing or two
that could prove useful.

19:01.807 --> 19:04.183
Why would I help the man
that killed my sister?

19:04.351 --> 19:07.687
Because you don't want me to become
the man who killed your boyfriend.

19:08.730 --> 19:10.648
MAN:
Sam's gonna stay here with pretty boy.

19:10.816 --> 19:14.068
Make sure you don't get any funny ideas,
because Samuel will kill you.

19:14.236 --> 19:15.236
Right, Samuel?

19:15.946 --> 19:17.989
Huh?
Oh, yeah, I'll kill you.

19:18.156 --> 19:19.240
[GUN COCKS]

19:19.449 --> 19:20.575
See?

19:22.244 --> 19:24.036
I’ll be okay.

19:24.204 --> 19:25.872
All right.

19:26.081 --> 19:28.499
Let's crash this party.

19:28.917 --> 19:30.251
[SAMUEL CHUCKLING]

19:31.086 --> 19:34.005
Get off. Get off me.

19:46.476 --> 19:47.977
[CREAKING AND THUDDING]

19:49.563 --> 19:51.063
[THUDDING AND METAL CLANGING]

19:52.274 --> 19:54.275
What's going on?

19:58.280 --> 19:59.780
KYLE:
Looks like we've got visitors.

20:01.033 --> 20:02.366
[HAMMER SIGHS]

20:10.834 --> 20:13.628
HAMMER:
Ariel. What are you doing here?

20:15.464 --> 20:16.631
Desmond.

20:20.802 --> 20:22.720
Oh, shit.

20:22.888 --> 20:25.306
Ariel, why did you
bring these people here?

20:25.807 --> 20:31.270
Mmm.... She didn't.
We just kind of let ourselves in.

20:32.981 --> 20:35.149
Guess what I found.

20:35.651 --> 20:37.652
What's going on? You know this asshole?

20:37.819 --> 20:40.947
Desmond Niles,
a former student of mine.

20:42.115 --> 20:46.827
"Asshole." That's not very friendly, Ariel.

20:47.287 --> 20:49.830
And actually, Richie boy...

20:50.707 --> 20:55.002
...nowadays, I'm not your student...

20:55.170 --> 20:56.837
...I'm your competition.

20:57.005 --> 21:00.341
Who's your buyer? Maxwell? Rupert?

21:00.801 --> 21:02.885
A gentleman never kisses and tells.

21:04.137 --> 21:08.265
This statue belongs in a museum,
not in the hands of some private collector.

21:08.433 --> 21:12.520
I got 5 million reasons that say otherwise.

21:14.523 --> 21:16.482
HAMMER:
How did you find out about the journal?

21:18.777 --> 21:21.153
This is where it gets ugly.

21:34.793 --> 21:36.127
Why am I not surprised?

21:38.296 --> 21:40.464
Michelle, what the hell's going on here?

21:42.259 --> 21:44.593
It's really simple, honey.

21:44.761 --> 21:47.054
I'm about to graduate.

21:47.389 --> 21:50.725
Am I gonna teach a bunch of freshmen...

21:50.892 --> 21:55.187
...the difference between Homo erectus...

21:55.355 --> 21:57.732
...and Homo sapiens?

21:57.899 --> 22:01.235
Or am I gonna sit on a yacht
and work on my tan?

22:02.070 --> 22:03.738
How can you be saying these things?

22:05.282 --> 22:06.365
HAMMER:
What did he do to you?

22:08.160 --> 22:10.786
-Everything?
-Yeah.

22:10.954 --> 22:13.080
That you were too busy to do.

22:13.248 --> 22:16.125
Jesus. I don't know you.

22:17.210 --> 22:19.587
You gonna leave
without giving me a goodbye kiss?

22:19.755 --> 22:21.422
[CLANGING AND HEAVY THUD]

22:21.757 --> 22:23.257
[METALLIC THUDDING]

22:23.925 --> 22:26.927
Did you hear that?
The house is going into lockdown.

22:27.095 --> 22:28.554
What are you talking about?

22:29.473 --> 22:32.558
Vannacutt installed a mechanism
that can seal up the whole asylum.

22:32.726 --> 22:35.895
Made it impossible for patients to escape.

22:36.480 --> 22:39.273
That's how Price's guests
got trapped in the first place.

22:39.816 --> 22:41.233
Good old Vannacutt.

22:42.027 --> 22:44.737
The field of medicine
wouldn't be the same without him.

22:44.905 --> 22:47.782
If this place goes into lockdown,
we'll be trapped.

22:48.366 --> 22:53.412
Well, that's why our first stop's
gonna be the master control room.

22:53.872 --> 22:55.706
Let the tour begin.

22:55.999 --> 22:57.333
[GPR BEEPING SLOWLY]

23:19.564 --> 23:21.816
Mansions with their own mental wards.

23:23.485 --> 23:25.611
Only in fucking L.A.

23:37.582 --> 23:40.084
[TORTURED SCREAM]

23:53.932 --> 23:55.766
How twisted.

24:14.202 --> 24:15.703
[TORTURED SCREAM]

24:21.543 --> 24:24.795
HAMMER: Having a hard time deciphering
Vannacutt's handwriting?

24:24.963 --> 24:26.505
You should let me take a look.

24:44.691 --> 24:45.733
Richard.

24:46.026 --> 24:47.026
[RICHARD YELLS]

24:47.777 --> 24:48.944
RICHARD:
Oh.

24:54.868 --> 24:58.329
Does anyone else wanna take a look?

24:58.663 --> 25:01.248
No? Okay. I didn't think so.

25:01.416 --> 25:04.668
As far as I can tell,
Vannacutt hid the idol...

25:04.836 --> 25:07.213
...in a secret chamber
deep in the basement.

25:07.380 --> 25:10.925
So why don't we all take a corridor...

25:11.635 --> 25:13.510
...and cover as much ground as possible?

25:13.678 --> 25:16.138
Whoa, time-out.

25:16.306 --> 25:18.766
Desmond, right?

25:21.436 --> 25:24.271
You're not seriously suggesting
that we all split up...

25:24.439 --> 25:27.942
...in a haunted house, are you?

25:29.861 --> 25:31.028
[GUN COCKS]

25:42.707 --> 25:44.959
WARREN:
Fucking shitty water.

25:46.044 --> 25:47.836
That's all I needed.

25:48.004 --> 25:50.297
Knee-high in shitty water.

25:50.465 --> 25:51.465
Thanks a lot.

25:52.968 --> 25:54.176
[GPR BEEPING SLOWLY]

26:01.893 --> 26:02.977
Come on, mate.

26:08.858 --> 26:10.317
You kind of look familiar to me.

26:18.159 --> 26:21.495
Oh, my God, I've got it.
You're "Notorious" Norris Boz, right?

26:21.663 --> 26:23.956
You were like
UFC heavyweight champ, dude.

26:24.958 --> 26:26.500
Yeah. Ha, ha, ha!

26:27.294 --> 26:29.420
Those were the good old days.
Heh, heh, heh.

26:29.587 --> 26:30.587
Ow.

26:30.797 --> 26:32.715
Yeah, good old days.

26:32.882 --> 26:33.924
[MIMICS ROARING]

26:34.092 --> 26:36.302
Just so you know, you fight like a girl.

26:36.469 --> 26:38.345
Like a lady.

26:42.600 --> 26:44.852
Oh, fuck this, mate. Come on, whatever.

26:45.020 --> 26:46.186
[SCREECHING]

26:49.858 --> 26:52.609
MICHELLE:
This place is something else, huh?

26:53.611 --> 26:55.612
Are you gonna mope all night long now?

26:55.780 --> 26:57.698
What could I possibly have to say to you?

26:57.866 --> 27:01.869
Don't be such a baby. The only thing
hurting you right now is your big ego.

27:02.871 --> 27:06.040
-How long has this been going on?
-Does it really matter?

27:06.583 --> 27:09.543
-I can't believe you're doing this.
-You'll get over it.

27:09.711 --> 27:11.045
I loved you, Michelle.

27:11.212 --> 27:13.547
The only thing you love, Richard, is you.

27:13.715 --> 27:15.549
It's time I looked out for myself.

27:15.717 --> 27:19.720
Yeah, well,
you seem to have a knack for that.

27:19.888 --> 27:21.722
Yeah, well, I learned from the best.

27:21.890 --> 27:23.223
[WHOOSHING]

27:34.402 --> 27:36.695
Come on, baby. Where are you?

27:37.739 --> 27:38.906
Where are you? Come on.

27:39.074 --> 27:41.575
[BREATHING AND MURMURING]

27:48.166 --> 27:50.250
There's something here.

27:52.045 --> 27:53.379
[GPR BEEPING FASTER]

27:53.755 --> 27:55.714
Where the fuck are you?

27:58.843 --> 28:00.094
[GPR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

28:00.261 --> 28:01.845
It's about fucking time.

28:02.013 --> 28:06.266
Five million dead presidents,
here I fucking come.

28:13.525 --> 28:15.025
[GROWLING]

28:15.902 --> 28:18.445
Yo, D. Can you read me?

28:18.613 --> 28:19.905
I think I got--

28:36.756 --> 28:38.590
[SCREAMING]

28:38.967 --> 28:40.092
God, no!

28:43.471 --> 28:45.889
God, no, no, no!

28:47.767 --> 28:49.768
[CRACKING AND SQUISHING]

29:02.407 --> 29:07.161
So your sister,
she really believed in ghosts, huh?

29:07.328 --> 29:09.329
Leave me the fuck alone.

29:11.583 --> 29:14.126
Call me crazy if you like...

29:14.711 --> 29:18.005
...but I only believe in what I can see...

29:18.173 --> 29:20.257
...and touch...

29:22.343 --> 29:24.303
...and taste.

29:26.556 --> 29:29.516
You really don't like me now, do you?

29:34.939 --> 29:36.273
[DISTANT METALLIC CLANGING]

29:37.233 --> 29:38.609
[GPR BEEPING SLOWLY]

29:52.707 --> 29:54.041
[BREATHING]

30:13.394 --> 30:15.437
Kinky shit.

30:27.242 --> 30:28.242
What the hell?

30:42.715 --> 30:44.216
Stay right where you are.

30:44.384 --> 30:46.927
Don't fucking move.

30:50.640 --> 30:52.808
Who the hell are you?

30:54.435 --> 30:56.395
How did you get in here?

31:05.822 --> 31:07.781
Holy shit.

31:28.469 --> 31:29.636
[GHOSTLY VOICES MURMURING]

31:32.348 --> 31:33.515
[MOANING]

31:33.975 --> 31:35.142
[GHOSTLY BREATHING]

31:52.493 --> 31:53.952
[PANTING AND MOANING]

32:14.182 --> 32:15.182
[GIRL SCREAMS]

32:29.197 --> 32:31.198
[GASPS AND TORTURED SCREAMS]

32:33.242 --> 32:34.242
[YELLS]

32:36.788 --> 32:38.121
[HARUE YELLING AND GRUNTING]

32:52.345 --> 32:53.470
[GASPS]

33:05.817 --> 33:06.817
[GUNSHOT]

33:08.069 --> 33:09.069
DESMOND:
Shit.

33:09.904 --> 33:12.531
Desmond to Norris, do you copy?

33:13.116 --> 33:14.741
DESMOND [OVER RADIO]:
Norris, answer me, goddamn it!

33:14.909 --> 33:17.244
Desmond, I'm here, mate.
What's going on? Come on.

33:17.412 --> 33:19.621
-Hello?
DESMOND: Look, I need you to head back.

33:19.789 --> 33:21.915
Meet me in the main salon.
I heard gunshots.

33:22.667 --> 33:24.126
Warren, Harue, can you read me?

33:25.253 --> 33:27.045
Do you copy?

33:27.213 --> 33:30.048
Warren, Harue, can you read me?
What's going on?

33:35.555 --> 33:36.847
Shit.

33:40.727 --> 33:41.727
DESMOND:
Do it, Ariel.

33:42.562 --> 33:43.562
Open the door.

34:14.469 --> 34:15.635
[SCREAMING]

34:18.347 --> 34:19.347
[ARIEL SCREAMING]

34:25.188 --> 34:26.605
What the fuck happened?

34:26.938 --> 34:29.983
Exactly what my sister said
would happen.

34:33.987 --> 34:35.447
You okay?

34:40.119 --> 34:42.661
How did she get that thing on by herself?

34:47.835 --> 34:50.085
DESMOND [OVER RADIO]:
Samuel, we need you in the house.

34:52.089 --> 34:53.965
Is everything okay in there?

34:54.132 --> 34:56.009
Come into the house.

34:56.677 --> 35:00.514
Shit. Okay, looks like we're gonna
get wet, pretty boy. Let's go.

35:00.681 --> 35:02.682
All this time, I thought she was crazy.

35:03.184 --> 35:06.353
My sister was telling the truth
about this place.

35:10.691 --> 35:13.985
-We're not alone in this house.
-What the hell is she babbling about?

35:14.654 --> 35:16.154
I saw a man.

35:16.322 --> 35:18.240
He was a patient here.

35:18.407 --> 35:21.868
I think he led an uprising
the night that the hospital burnt down.

35:22.036 --> 35:24.037
I think he was trying
to stop Dr. Vannacutt.

35:25.248 --> 35:27.332
Okay, it's official. You're fucking crazy.

35:27.500 --> 35:29.042
DESMOND:
All right, enough of this.

35:29.210 --> 35:32.379
Enough. Let's go back upstairs
and find the others.

35:33.214 --> 35:35.632
-Come on, move.
MICHELLE: Let's go.

35:43.891 --> 35:47.310
NORRIS: Desmond, mate.
We're back upstairs in the main area.

35:47.478 --> 35:49.104
Desmond?

35:50.356 --> 35:51.356
Hey.

35:52.775 --> 35:54.234
The fuck was that?

36:02.201 --> 36:03.368
[PANTING]

36:16.591 --> 36:19.259
-Ha, ha, ha.
-Whew. Huh.

36:19.677 --> 36:21.428
It's nothing, mate.

36:23.723 --> 36:26.266
This place is ass-fucking my mind.

36:27.768 --> 36:29.728
Desmond, mate. Come in, where are you?

36:30.313 --> 36:32.105
[GHOSTLY BREATHING]

36:34.775 --> 36:35.775
What the--?

36:36.444 --> 36:37.736
NORRIS:
Ow.

36:37.903 --> 36:39.946
[GRUNTING]

36:43.117 --> 36:44.784
NORRIS:
Fuck!

36:45.453 --> 36:47.412
-Oh, my God.
NORRIS: Hey, mate, help me out.

36:50.916 --> 36:52.417
NORRIS:
Get them off me!

36:55.296 --> 36:56.796
[NORRIS GRUNTING AND YELLING]

36:57.923 --> 36:59.799
Fucking help me, mate, come on.

37:00.551 --> 37:01.885
-Fuck.
NORRIS: Help!

37:02.053 --> 37:03.470
[GLASS BREAKING]

37:04.722 --> 37:05.722
[GRUNTS]

37:07.224 --> 37:09.309
Help me, man! Ah!

37:18.736 --> 37:19.944
[TORTURED SCREAM]

37:32.083 --> 37:35.043
[SCREAMING]

37:46.055 --> 37:47.222
MICHELLE:
Holy shit.

37:47.390 --> 37:48.807
Kyle?

37:49.475 --> 37:52.018
Aah!
Shit.

37:53.729 --> 37:54.854
Where the hell's Norris?

37:55.523 --> 37:57.148
I think you're standing in Norris.

37:57.566 --> 37:58.817
[SQUISHING]

38:07.702 --> 38:09.994
Norris, where the hell are you?

38:10.746 --> 38:13.498
Warren, Harue. Goddamn it,
will one of you guys answer me?

38:15.126 --> 38:16.126
[CREAKING]

38:16.669 --> 38:16.960
Kyle, what happened here?

38:16.961 --> 38:19.879
Kyle, what happened here?

38:21.173 --> 38:22.924
Oh, God.

38:29.640 --> 38:30.765
Hey.

38:31.726 --> 38:33.935
It's true, isn't it?

38:34.854 --> 38:35.895
The house, it's--

38:36.063 --> 38:37.063
[METALLIC CLANGS AND THUDS]

38:37.565 --> 38:40.233
[GROANING AND CLANGING]

38:41.777 --> 38:42.944
[HEAVY THUDS]

38:56.834 --> 38:58.585
[LAUGHING]

38:59.044 --> 39:01.087
[PANTING]

39:07.261 --> 39:08.762
[DOORS THUDDING]

39:09.096 --> 39:10.096
DESMOND:
Fuck.

39:25.738 --> 39:27.614
What the fuck is going on?

39:27.782 --> 39:29.699
You took care
of the lockdown mechanism.

39:30.284 --> 39:32.494
What the hell are you doing in here?

39:33.370 --> 39:36.122
The fuck are you doing here?
I told you to stay in the car.

39:43.631 --> 39:45.298
Paul?

39:45.466 --> 39:47.592
Paul. Paul.

39:47.760 --> 39:49.219
No.

39:49.386 --> 39:51.179
No.

39:51.347 --> 39:54.307
No. No. No!

39:58.646 --> 40:00.480
GHOSTLY VOICES:
Ariel.

40:31.887 --> 40:34.055
Fuck you too.

40:40.020 --> 40:42.897
-Hey, back off. You told me to come in.
DESMOND: I did no such thing.

40:43.065 --> 40:46.276
SAMUEL: I spoke to you on the two-way.
-Whoever you talked to, it wasn't me.

40:46.443 --> 40:48.444
ARIEL:
It was the house.

40:50.781 --> 40:52.115
Ariel.

40:52.283 --> 40:54.617
-Oh, thank God. Are you okay?
-Yeah.

40:54.785 --> 40:56.369
PAUL:
Hey.

40:57.204 --> 40:58.705
How did you get back in here?

41:01.041 --> 41:02.876
The house wanted me to return.

41:03.377 --> 41:06.212
So what?
You just walked straight back in.

41:06.380 --> 41:09.173
-You're crazy.
-I don't leave my friends behind.

41:09.758 --> 41:11.259
Yeah. How touching.

41:11.760 --> 41:11.801
[GHOSTLY MURMUR]

41:11.802 --> 41:13.094
[GHOSTLY MURMUR]

41:14.763 --> 41:17.557
Wait, the house wanted you to--?
I don't-- The house?

41:17.725 --> 41:20.894
Look, according to my sister,
last time it was seeking revenge.

41:21.061 --> 41:24.397
Going after the descendants
of the orderlies that escaped the fire.

41:24.565 --> 41:26.691
But this time is different.

41:26.859 --> 41:28.151
[GHOSTLY VOICES]

41:29.278 --> 41:31.821
What's wrong with you?
There's no such thing as ghosts.

41:32.656 --> 41:35.742
Dude. I just saw one of your guerrillas
ripped to little pieces.

41:35.910 --> 41:39.579
-This shit is as real as it fucking gets.
-Somebody's playing a game with us.

41:39.747 --> 41:41.497
Don't you get it? All right?

41:41.665 --> 41:44.083
I bet it's Warren, all right?
Greedy little fucker.

41:44.251 --> 41:46.419
He's probably playing a trick on us, right?

41:46.587 --> 41:47.837
I mean-- Fucking prick.

41:48.005 --> 41:50.131
And I bet the whole lot is in on it.
All right?

41:50.299 --> 41:52.258
You're so in denial, man.

41:52.760 --> 41:55.929
You know what? He's right.
Your team has nothing to do with this.

41:56.096 --> 41:57.847
My guess is they're all dead.

41:58.015 --> 41:59.515
[GHOSTLY MURMURING]

42:00.142 --> 42:01.476
[RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]

42:10.361 --> 42:12.111
Where's Samuel?

42:13.822 --> 42:15.990
Wasn't he right behind me?

42:17.785 --> 42:19.202
Then there were six.

42:19.370 --> 42:21.621
DESMOND:
Samuel, where the fuck are you?

42:21.956 --> 42:23.122
[PANTING]

42:24.208 --> 42:25.875
Oh, fuck. What the fuck?

42:26.627 --> 42:30.213
You crazy bitch. Help!

42:30.381 --> 42:32.799
You crazy fuck.

42:32.967 --> 42:34.968
Let me out of the fucking chair!

42:36.303 --> 42:39.305
Samuel, answer, and right fucking now.

42:39.974 --> 42:41.474
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

42:46.438 --> 42:47.438
Who is it?

42:50.025 --> 42:51.359
[SECOND CELL PHONE RINGING]

42:52.987 --> 42:54.320
[THIRD CELL PHONE RINGING]

43:01.662 --> 43:02.829
[FOURTH CELL PHONE RINGING]

43:05.332 --> 43:06.499
[ALL CELL PHONES RINGING]

43:07.710 --> 43:10.044
[FIFTH CELL PHONE CHIMING
"MARY HAD A LITTLE LAMB"]

43:18.387 --> 43:19.679
ALL:
Hello?

43:19.847 --> 43:23.474
[SAMUEL SCREAMING]

43:28.355 --> 43:29.689
SAMUEL:
This isn't real.

43:31.567 --> 43:32.692
[PANTING]

43:33.610 --> 43:35.194
SAMUEL:
Or is it?

43:35.612 --> 43:37.071
What are you doing?

43:46.290 --> 43:47.665
Stop it. Stop--

43:47.875 --> 43:49.709
Wait. Wait. Wait.

43:54.715 --> 43:56.340
[GHOSTLY VOICE]

43:59.636 --> 44:03.890
Listen. Is there any way we can reverse
the lockdown mechanism?

44:04.600 --> 44:06.559
I doubt the house is gonna let us do that.

44:06.727 --> 44:08.728
You know what?
Fuck this. I'm out of here.

44:09.980 --> 44:12.899
Nobody goes anywhere until we get
what we came for, understand?

44:17.821 --> 44:21.657
Really? Little girls with big guns
only look good in movies, kid.

44:21.825 --> 44:23.743
Shut the fuck up.

44:24.119 --> 44:25.536
You're not a killer, Ariel.

44:25.704 --> 44:26.788
Really? Are you sure?

44:26.955 --> 44:29.248
You're the scumbag who killed my sister.

44:29.416 --> 44:33.878
Let's just relax and put those guns down
before someone gets hurt.

44:34.630 --> 44:39.217
There's a $5 million check out there
with my name on it, and I intend to cash it.

44:39.384 --> 44:41.427
Really? Five million dollars?

44:41.595 --> 44:43.763
Is that how much
my sister's life was worth?

44:44.098 --> 44:48.434
Our only chance of getting out of here
in one piece is if we work together.

44:50.354 --> 44:52.021
Too bad I'm not a team player,
Richie boy.

44:52.189 --> 44:53.940
-Say bye-bye.
MICHELLE: Desmond, watch out!

44:54.108 --> 44:55.441
[GUNSHOT]

44:55.776 --> 44:56.776
[GUNSHOT]

44:57.361 --> 44:58.903
Fuck.

45:00.030 --> 45:01.364
[PANTING AND GASPING]

45:02.616 --> 45:04.033
DESMOND:
Shit. Fuck. Fuck.

45:07.579 --> 45:08.704
Fuck.

45:12.918 --> 45:15.461
I'd be careful with that if I was you.

45:16.296 --> 45:18.214
That was for Sara.

45:18.924 --> 45:21.259
Keep an eye on them, will you?

45:22.136 --> 45:23.803
No problem.

45:25.097 --> 45:26.722
ARIEL:
According to these blueprints...

45:26.890 --> 45:30.476
...the asylum was connected
to a water-supply system in 1 897.

45:30.644 --> 45:33.479
There's a sewer tunnel
that runs underneath the house.

45:33.856 --> 45:35.565
Go on.

45:36.358 --> 45:40.486
Well, the shower area is located
above the drainage system.

45:40.654 --> 45:43.906
I bet we could find a sewer grate
down there that we could access.

45:44.825 --> 45:45.992
Hey, that could work.

45:47.286 --> 45:49.954
ARIEL: All right. So the quickest way
to the shower area...

45:50.122 --> 45:53.374
...is through the hydrotherapy room,
down the east corridor...

45:53.542 --> 45:55.793
...and up another hallway. Here.

45:55.961 --> 45:57.920
Yeah, that looks easy enough.

45:59.756 --> 46:03.467
The house is gonna do
everything in its power to stop us.

46:03.677 --> 46:06.762
Of course.
Because that's what houses do.

46:08.724 --> 46:10.600
I just had a thought.

46:10.767 --> 46:13.019
I remember Vannacutt
mentioning in his journal...

46:13.187 --> 46:15.646
...that the Baphomet idol
was guarded by the dead.

46:15.814 --> 46:19.817
I figured he was speaking metaphorically,
now I'm not so sure, because guess what.

46:20.777 --> 46:23.321
-There's a crematorium in the basement.
KYLE: Wait a minute.

46:23.488 --> 46:27.617
Why the hell would there be
a crematorium inside a mental asylum?

46:27.784 --> 46:32.038
I know during the tuberculosis epidemic,
the institute took in regular patients.

46:32.206 --> 46:34.290
Presumably,
some were cremated in the hospital...

46:34.458 --> 46:36.542
...in order to minimize further infection.

46:36.710 --> 46:39.921
So if we find the crematorium,
we find the idol.

46:40.088 --> 46:43.216
I don't give a damn about the idol.
I care about getting out alive.

46:44.051 --> 46:47.720
What about you, Richard?
Is that all you care about?

46:48.222 --> 46:51.557
Are you really gonna let
this opportunity pass you by?

46:51.725 --> 46:54.185
We're talking about the Baphomet idol.

46:55.187 --> 46:57.897
DESMOND: The prize you've been chasing
all these years.

46:58.982 --> 47:01.275
Personally, I don't think you can.

47:02.444 --> 47:04.403
I know you too well.

47:07.074 --> 47:08.532
It's your life's work.

47:10.452 --> 47:14.705
If you guys wanna get yourselves killed
chasing after this stupid thing, be my guest.

47:14.873 --> 47:16.207
Paul and I are getting out.

47:18.460 --> 47:19.919
ARIEL:
So, what's it gonna be?

47:22.464 --> 47:24.548
I'm coming with you.

47:25.509 --> 47:29.929
HAMMER: Vannacutt was known for being
a brilliant physician and great humanitarian.

47:30.097 --> 47:32.556
Nominated for the Nobel Prize in the '20s.

47:32.724 --> 47:36.936
But somehow, this great man went from
saving people to butchering them.

47:37.104 --> 47:38.771
Why?

47:38.939 --> 47:41.857
Um, I have a theory. Maybe he was nuts?

47:43.151 --> 47:47.613
The Church believed the statue
possessed an evil influence over men.

47:47.781 --> 47:50.408
Those who wanted its power
were susceptible.

47:50.575 --> 47:54.620
Are you saying this statue corrupted
Vannacutt and his staff somehow?

47:55.122 --> 47:56.580
Crazy, huh?

48:34.661 --> 48:37.163
KYLE:
What the fuck did they use this for?

48:37.331 --> 48:39.123
Hydro-pool therapy.

48:39.833 --> 48:41.459
Hydro-what?

48:41.626 --> 48:45.129
HAMMER: One of Vannacutt's special
contributions to modern medicine.

48:46.381 --> 48:49.884
Expose a patient to a pool
filled with freezing water.

48:50.052 --> 48:53.804
Replace internal pain with external pain
and they'll cancel each other out.

48:53.972 --> 48:57.475
Nice. Wonder why it didn't catch on.

48:57.642 --> 48:58.976
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

48:59.978 --> 49:01.687
Shut up.

49:04.107 --> 49:05.441
[GHOSTLY NOISES]

49:09.946 --> 49:11.405
[ELECTRICAL HUMMING
AND BUZZING]

49:19.873 --> 49:21.165
What's going on?

49:24.544 --> 49:25.711
Richard.

49:30.050 --> 49:32.343
No, you shut up.

49:44.564 --> 49:46.524
MICHELLE:
I got the map, Desmond. Let's go.

49:46.691 --> 49:47.817
[GUNSHOTS]

49:57.536 --> 49:58.536
PAUL:
Ariel.

50:04.084 --> 50:05.418
PAUL:
Ariel.

50:08.088 --> 50:10.589
Kyle. Kyle. Please, Kyle.

50:10.757 --> 50:13.259
Ariel. Hold on.

50:13.885 --> 50:15.511
Kyle.

50:17.055 --> 50:18.347
Kyle.

50:19.349 --> 50:21.100
[GASPING AND COUGHING]

50:21.685 --> 50:23.936
ARIEL: Guys, you gotta find a way
to get us out of here.

50:24.729 --> 50:25.896
[GHOSTLY VOICES]

50:33.738 --> 50:35.448
[GASPING AND PANTING]

50:50.422 --> 50:51.422
Ariel.

51:01.641 --> 51:04.643
KYLE:
Oh, God. Please, wait.

51:06.980 --> 51:08.606
[CREAKING]

51:11.526 --> 51:14.236
-I can't. I can't.
PAUL: I can't reach you.

51:17.782 --> 51:20.493
Aah! Holy shit.

51:36.176 --> 51:38.177
[SCREECHES]

51:38.345 --> 51:39.512
[ARIEL SCREAMS]

51:50.065 --> 51:51.732
[SCREAMS]

51:57.864 --> 52:00.157
KYLE:
I’ll kill you, you bitch!

52:01.243 --> 52:03.035
Kyle.

52:04.913 --> 52:07.373
Kyle!

52:21.179 --> 52:22.179
[GASPS]

52:28.436 --> 52:29.645
ARIEL:
Help me.

52:35.151 --> 52:36.902
ARIEL:
Hurry.

52:40.407 --> 52:42.408
[GHOSTLY SHRIEKS]

52:49.749 --> 52:50.916
[ARIEL GASPING]

52:53.128 --> 52:55.254
ARIEL:
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

52:59.092 --> 53:00.843
PAUL:
Okay.

53:16.818 --> 53:19.278
You have no idea where we are, do you?

53:19.446 --> 53:24.074
I would if you kept your trap shut
for one second, sweetheart.

53:25.452 --> 53:28.454
How hard can it be
to find a goddamn crematorium?

53:28.622 --> 53:30.706
It's on the map, isn't it?

53:31.082 --> 53:32.291
I’ll get us there.

53:32.459 --> 53:35.127
You mean
if the house doesn't get us first.

53:35.295 --> 53:37.796
-Getting a little superstitious?
-No, of course not.

53:37.964 --> 53:39.757
But why aren't your men answering you?

53:39.924 --> 53:43.552
Look, I already told you.
They're probably after the idol themselves.

53:43.720 --> 53:46.221
Maybe, but why not find the idol
and then turn on us?

53:46.389 --> 53:47.640
It doesn't make any sense.

53:47.891 --> 53:50.059
That crazy bitch is finally getting to you.

53:54.731 --> 53:56.732
Or maybe....

54:00.779 --> 54:02.946
Or maybe you're part of this.

54:05.492 --> 54:07.368
Why are you looking at me like that?

54:07.535 --> 54:10.329
You're trying to tell me
that you suddenly believe in ghosts?

54:10.497 --> 54:11.664
[METALLIC CLICK]

54:14.167 --> 54:15.167
What are you doing?

54:16.378 --> 54:18.337
That's it, isn't it?

54:18.963 --> 54:21.090
You're looking to play me
like you did Richard.

54:21.257 --> 54:24.426
-Desmond, don't be ridiculous.
-How do I know you're not with them?

54:24.594 --> 54:26.303
Desmond, put the gun away.

54:26.471 --> 54:28.847
Betray one man,
how soon before the next?

54:29.015 --> 54:32.017
Jesus Christ, Desmond, it's me.
Put the goddamn gun down.

54:32.185 --> 54:34.103
-Get them on the radio.
-What?

54:34.270 --> 54:36.522
Put whoever's behind this
on the goddamn radio.

54:36.690 --> 54:39.525
-You're not making any sense, you're crazy.
-Put them on!

54:39.693 --> 54:41.694
-There's nothing going on.
-Put them on the radio!

54:41.861 --> 54:42.861
[GUNSHOTS]

54:43.029 --> 54:44.446
MICHELLE:
Oh, my God!

54:51.996 --> 54:53.330
Michelle!

54:56.668 --> 54:57.876
ARIEL:
Jesus.

54:58.044 --> 54:59.712
Why didn't those things
come after us?

54:59.879 --> 55:01.380
HAMMER:
I don't know.

55:01.548 --> 55:05.259
But I think some of these souls
are reliving their final moments...

55:05.427 --> 55:06.802
...over and over again.

55:06.970 --> 55:09.680
Trapped in the place where they died.

55:11.015 --> 55:13.225
Thanks for saving my life back there.

55:13.977 --> 55:15.686
ARIEL:
Both of you.

55:17.731 --> 55:19.398
Are you okay?

55:21.818 --> 55:24.403
I convinced Kyle to come along for this.

55:24.571 --> 55:26.196
The kid's dead because of me.

55:26.740 --> 55:28.240
Don't say that.

55:28.408 --> 55:31.201
You didn't kill Kyle. Desmond did.

55:31.411 --> 55:32.578
[SNORTS LIGHTLY]

55:36.082 --> 55:38.834
You think you can get us out of here
without the blueprints?

55:40.545 --> 55:42.087
I’ll give it my best shot.

55:43.298 --> 55:44.673
Goddamn it, Desmond.

55:44.841 --> 55:45.841
[PANTING]

55:56.644 --> 55:58.604
DESMOND:
Michelle!

55:59.189 --> 56:01.231
Michelle!

56:18.291 --> 56:20.042
Oh, my God.

56:20.210 --> 56:22.002
Oh, my God.

56:33.807 --> 56:34.973
[WOOD CREAKING]

57:13.471 --> 57:14.680
[SQUISHING AND DRIPPING]

57:30.363 --> 57:32.281
This must be it.

57:44.961 --> 57:47.546
PAUL:
Hey, I found something.

57:57.890 --> 58:00.058
Okay, help me lift it.

58:04.772 --> 58:06.857
[ALL GRUNT]

58:08.359 --> 58:12.571
-I don't think that's gonna happen.
-It has to. It's the only way out.

58:13.615 --> 58:15.407
ARIEL:
Damn it.

58:40.725 --> 58:43.518
Destroy the statue.

58:55.406 --> 58:56.948
Ariel, what is it? You okay?

58:57.283 --> 58:58.617
We can't leave.

58:58.785 --> 59:00.285
What?

59:00.620 --> 59:04.206
-I know how to make it stop.
-What are you talking about?

59:04.374 --> 59:07.876
The spirits here. They wanna be at peace,
but the evil won't let them.

59:08.378 --> 59:10.504
You're talking about Vannacutt.

59:11.589 --> 59:13.965
Vannacutt is just a servant.

59:14.133 --> 59:16.134
Of Baphomet.

59:16.511 --> 59:19.388
That's why my sister was trying to
help you find the statue.

59:19.555 --> 59:21.932
The idol is the heart of this place.

59:22.100 --> 59:24.810
You destroy it,
you break Baphomet's hold.

59:25.853 --> 59:28.772
ARIEL:
It's the only way to defeat the house.

59:56.342 --> 59:58.343
What do we do now?

59:59.053 --> 01:00:02.347
One of these furnaces
has a chamber that leads to the idol.

01:00:04.225 --> 01:00:07.185
PAUL: You're saying we have to crawl
into one of these things?

01:00:09.313 --> 01:00:10.981
Yeah.

01:00:11.691 --> 01:00:13.692
Yeah, it's the only way.

01:00:22.034 --> 01:00:23.827
This is it.

01:00:28.040 --> 01:00:30.041
ARIEL:
This is the entrance.

01:00:44.182 --> 01:00:46.183
You ready to do this?

01:00:46.851 --> 01:00:49.019
Ready as I'll ever be.

01:00:52.356 --> 01:00:53.982
Listen, um....

01:00:54.901 --> 01:00:57.736
-If we don't make it out of here, I--
-We'll make it.

01:00:58.070 --> 01:01:01.364
If we don't make it,
I just want you to know that--

01:01:02.366 --> 01:01:03.658
What?

01:01:03.826 --> 01:01:05.827
That, uh....

01:01:06.162 --> 01:01:09.915
That you make a lot of typos
for the editor of a magazine?

01:01:10.458 --> 01:01:12.709
It's okay.
Like half your staff know by now.

01:01:17.799 --> 01:01:20.383
All right, you two,
I'm getting all choked up over here.

01:01:21.093 --> 01:01:23.053
HAMMER:
Let's do this.

01:01:45.201 --> 01:01:47.285
I think we're almost there.

01:02:44.510 --> 01:02:47.596
PAUL:
Jesus. What the hell is this stuff?

01:02:49.599 --> 01:02:51.766
HAMMER:
It seems to be organic.

01:02:53.352 --> 01:02:55.437
The heart of the house.

01:03:04.322 --> 01:03:05.488
[GHOSTLY WHISPERING]

01:03:05.823 --> 01:03:06.990
It's remarkable.

01:03:16.876 --> 01:03:18.627
ARIEL:
What are you doing?

01:03:22.882 --> 01:03:25.467
Richard, what are you doing?

01:03:27.887 --> 01:03:29.888
Richard, step aside.

01:03:30.056 --> 01:03:31.723
Richard.

01:03:32.725 --> 01:03:35.518
ARIEL:
I have to destroy it. I said, move.

01:03:35.686 --> 01:03:38.063
Hey, Richard. Hey.

01:03:38.230 --> 01:03:39.856
PAUL:
Jesus, hey.

01:03:40.024 --> 01:03:41.358
Hey.

01:03:42.109 --> 01:03:43.735
Richard.

01:03:46.572 --> 01:03:50.116
Step aside. Uh-huh.

01:03:50.284 --> 01:03:51.743
Yeah.

01:03:54.413 --> 01:03:55.914
HAMMER:
It was calling me.

01:03:56.082 --> 01:03:58.667
I could feel its power.

01:04:07.927 --> 01:04:09.386
ARIEL:
Damn it.

01:04:09.553 --> 01:04:12.472
PAUL:
Shit, you didn't even scratch it.

01:04:14.100 --> 01:04:17.435
If we can't destroy the statue,
then maybe there's another way.

01:04:17.937 --> 01:04:19.437
Such as?

01:04:21.607 --> 01:04:22.691
Well...

01:04:22.858 --> 01:04:25.110
...as long as the Baphomet idol
is in the house...

01:04:25.277 --> 01:04:27.612
...the souls are trapped here, right?

01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:29.906
So, what happens if we remove it?

01:04:30.074 --> 01:04:32.158
How do you plan on doing that?

01:04:32.326 --> 01:04:34.452
In case you hadn't noticed,
we can't get out.

01:04:34.620 --> 01:04:37.539
Yeah. We noticed.

01:04:38.749 --> 01:04:40.583
The sewer tunnel.

01:04:40.751 --> 01:04:43.378
The statue is small enough
to fit through the grate.

01:04:43.796 --> 01:04:45.630
I don't know about this.

01:04:45.798 --> 01:04:48.425
ARIEL: Well, do you have
any better suggestions?

01:04:49.677 --> 01:04:51.469
I say it's worth a shot.

01:04:54.306 --> 01:04:55.974
All right.

01:05:13.951 --> 01:05:15.452
[BOTH GRUNTING AND STRAINING]

01:05:15.619 --> 01:05:16.953
[GHOSTLY SHRIEKING]

01:05:19.999 --> 01:05:22.000
[SHRIEKS AND MURMURS]

01:05:26.589 --> 01:05:28.423
ARIEL:
I don't think we're alone anymore.

01:05:28.591 --> 01:05:29.632
Let's go.

01:05:55.993 --> 01:05:56.993
Going somewhere?

01:05:57.453 --> 01:05:58.870
We don't have time for this.

01:05:59.038 --> 01:06:00.497
DESMOND:
Yeah, well, you better make time.

01:06:03.209 --> 01:06:04.209
Is that it?

01:06:04.835 --> 01:06:07.712
Well, Richard, I knew
you wouldn't leave without it.

01:06:07.922 --> 01:06:09.756
[GHOSTLY CHANTING]

01:06:10.633 --> 01:06:12.300
[GHOSTLY MOAN]

01:06:12.468 --> 01:06:14.469
All right, come on. Give it to me.

01:06:15.888 --> 01:06:17.555
Come on.

01:06:17.723 --> 01:06:19.724
Give it to me, now!

01:06:20.559 --> 01:06:21.643
[GROWL]

01:06:21.811 --> 01:06:22.852
DESMOND:
Come on.

01:06:23.437 --> 01:06:24.896
Come on.

01:06:26.315 --> 01:06:27.774
What?

01:06:48.337 --> 01:06:49.963
DESMOND:
No! No!

01:06:50.131 --> 01:06:53.925
No! No!

01:06:54.093 --> 01:06:57.095
No! No! No!

01:06:58.264 --> 01:07:00.265
[SCREAMING]

01:07:09.692 --> 01:07:12.110
ARIEL: Run!
PAUL: Oh, shit.

01:07:15.739 --> 01:07:16.865
Paul!

01:07:20.369 --> 01:07:22.954
Keep going. Get the idol out of here,
I’ll be all right.

01:07:24.456 --> 01:07:25.456
Go!

01:07:53.694 --> 01:07:54.819
No!

01:08:04.830 --> 01:08:06.164
What are you doing?

01:08:06.332 --> 01:08:08.917
I've been looking for this statue
for 20 years.

01:08:09.084 --> 01:08:10.335
It belongs to me.

01:08:10.502 --> 01:08:13.588
Richard, if we don't do this,
we're all gonna die.

01:08:15.299 --> 01:08:17.300
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:08:32.149 --> 01:08:33.608
[GHOSTLY CHANTING]

01:09:00.219 --> 01:09:01.551
[GHOSTLY GROWLING]

01:09:05.099 --> 01:09:06.432
[GHOSTLY BREATHS]

01:09:11.563 --> 01:09:12.729
[GROWL]

01:09:22.741 --> 01:09:24.325
Richard, get off me!

01:09:29.331 --> 01:09:31.416
You can fight it.

01:09:36.921 --> 01:09:38.006
ARIEL:
Fight it.

01:09:38.424 --> 01:09:39.590
Fight it!

01:10:03.157 --> 01:10:04.782
HAMMER:
Ariel.

01:10:04.950 --> 01:10:05.950
Ariel, I'm okay.

01:10:13.834 --> 01:10:15.626
HAMMER:
Ariel, wake up.

01:10:27.139 --> 01:10:30.058
HAMMER:
Ariel, the idol.

01:11:09.932 --> 01:11:11.599
Oh, God. Oh, God.

01:11:59.731 --> 01:12:00.731
VANNACUTT:
No.

01:12:02.443 --> 01:12:04.694
No. No!

01:12:07.906 --> 01:12:08.906
[GHOSTLY SHRIEKS]

01:12:49.865 --> 01:12:52.950
-Paul.
-Ariel.

01:13:27.152 --> 01:13:28.486
Come on.

01:13:41.416 --> 01:13:42.750
[BOTH PANTING]

01:13:54.054 --> 01:13:55.930
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:13:57.808 --> 01:13:59.392
PAUL:
Hey.

01:13:59.601 --> 01:14:01.477
What is it? You okay?

01:14:01.645 --> 01:14:05.273
Baphomet's evil has been trapped
in that house for over 50 years.

01:14:05.857 --> 01:14:07.775
We set it free.

01:14:09.486 --> 01:14:10.987
You're--

01:14:11.280 --> 01:14:13.114
You're saying the house--

01:14:13.282 --> 01:14:15.783
The house wanted us to succeed?

01:14:18.370 --> 01:14:20.037
I don't know.

01:14:24.376 --> 01:14:57.806
ARIEL:
Let's go home.

01:19:58.793 --> 01:19:59.150
[GIGGLING]

01:19:59.151 --> 01:20:00.026
[GIGGLING]

01:20:44.321 --> 01:20:46.989
WOMAN: What is it?
MAN: I don't know.

01:20:47.157 --> 01:20:49.867
I think it might be worth something.

01:20:52.287 --> 01:20:53.621
[GHOSTLY VOICES]
